pullRequest.body:
In the new file `CategoryTheory.Localization.Triangulated`, it is shown that if a class of morphisms `W` in a pretriangulated category is compatible with the triangulation and has a left calculus of fractions, then the localized category is also pretriangulated.

---

- [x] depends on: #11737
- [x] depends on: #11721
- [x] depends on: #11728

I think this can be an instance?
I found it convenient to restate it in the `Triangulated.Localization` namespace.
In that case, maybe put the `alias` below the original lemma or just rename it altogether?

```suggestion
  refine ⟨L.obj Z, e.inv.right ≫ L.map g,
    L.map h ≫ (L.commShiftIso (1 : ℤ)).hom.app _ ≫ e.hom.left⟦(1 : ℤ)⟧', _, ?_, H⟩
  refine Triangle.isoMk _ _ (Arrow.leftFunc.mapIso e.symm) (Arrow.rightFunc.mapIso e.symm)
    (Iso.refl _) e.inv.w.symm (by simp) ?_
```
I might be wrong here.

```suggestion
  refine ⟨L.mapTriangle.map (completeDistinguishedTriangleMorphism T₁ T₃ hT₁ hT₃ α.f
      (γ.f ≫ σ) fac.symm) ≫ inv (L.mapTriangle.map ψ), ?_, ?_⟩
```
